cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.RO 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) because it introduces a new framework for solving the model agnostic meta learning (MAML) problem. It is also likely to belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) because it proposes a new algorithm for meta learning based on Evolution Strategies (ES) that can handle new types of nonsmooth adaptation operators. Additionally, the paper's empirical results show that the proposed ES-MAML algorithm is competitive with existing methods in computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) domains.
